  <div class="sqs-html-content" data-sqsp-text-block-content><h3 style="text-align:center;white-space:pre-wrap;"><strong>Acoustic Design by the Legendary Roger D’Arcy</strong></h3><p style="text-align:center;white-space:pre-wrap;" class="">Every inch of EBC has been acoustically treated by the renowned architect Roger D’Arcy, ensuring unparalleled sound quality. Whether you're recording an album, filming a music video, or staging a photoshoot, EBC delivers an exceptional experience with its full blackout facility and impeccable acoustics. Roger D'Arcy is an architect and acoustic designer with over 30 years of experience in the planning and architectural-acoustic design of recording studios. He’s Founder of Recording Architecture (RA), a UK-based firm specialising in studio design and Co-author of "Acoustic Design for the Home Studio" with Hugh Flynn. n addition to his architectural work, Roger D'Arcy is also a singer/songwriter. He has released several solo albums, including "Crooked Tales" (2016), "House of Heads" (2017), and "The Road To Stameen" (2019)</p><p style="text-align:center;white-space:pre-wrap;" class="">Roger D'Arcy's work in studio design has been widely recognised in the music industry. He has been described as an "international man of studio design" and his firm, Recording Architecture, has gained a reputation for innovative and high-quality studio designs. D'Arcy has designed studios around the world, with projects in over 40 countries.</p><p style="text-align:center;white-space:pre-wrap;" class="">Some notable studios designed by D'Arcy and his firm include:</p><ul data-rte-list="default"><li><p style="text-align:center;white-space:pre-wrap;" class="">Lansdowne Studios</p></li><li><p style="text-align:center;white-space:pre-wrap;" class="">CTS Studios</p></li><li><p style="text-align:center;white-space:pre-wrap;" class="">Installations for Abbey Road</p></li><li><p style="text-align:center;white-space:pre-wrap;" class="">Studios for EMI Music</p></li><li><p style="text-align:center;white-space:pre-wrap;" class="">Crystalphonic</p></li><li><p style="text-align:center;white-space:pre-wrap;" class="">Optimum Mastering</p></li></ul></div>


  
