  <div class="sqs-html-content" data-sqsp-text-block-content><h2 style="text-align:center;white-space:pre-wrap;"><strong>Welcome to Empire Broadcasting Corporation (EBC Studio) – East London's Premier Recording Studio</strong></h2><p style="text-align:center;white-space:pre-wrap;" class="sqsrte-large">EBC Music Studio positions itself as a premier destination for high-quality music production and recording, offering a unique combination of cutting-edge technology and artistic ambiance. The studio is designed to cater to a wide range of musical needs, from large orchestral recordings to intimate solo sessions, created by Marlon Brown and the exceptional acoustic design by Roger D’Arcy.</p><p style="text-align:center;white-space:pre-wrap;" class="" data-rte-preserve-empty="true"></p><p style="text-align:center;white-space:pre-wrap;" class="">Originally a historic Methodist church, this building has been transformed into a state-of-the-art, 1,500-square-foot soundproof live room. It features a dramatic 30-foot-high pine vaulted ceiling and a unique surrounding balcony.<br><strong>The Art of Marlon Alexander Brown<br></strong></p><p style="text-align:center;white-space:pre-wrap;" class="">Marlon is a contemporary multi-disciplinary artist whose work delves deep into the realms of surrealism, social commentary, and existential exploration. His creations invite viewers to ponder the complexities of modern life, spirituality, and human nature. His work also reflects an acute awareness of contemporary issues—ranging from economic disparities to environmental concerns—often conveyed through satirical depictions or allegorical scenarios. This approach not only critiques but also encourages reflection on our collective responsibilities as global citizens.</p><p style="text-align:center;white-space:pre-wrap;" class=""><strong>Performance Art</strong> <br><br>His performative acts blur the lines between art and activism. By holding signs with provocative messages like 'THE BEGINNING IS NIGH' or 'THOU SHALT NOT BANK,' his art enters public spaces and sparks dialogue among audiences. These performances are integral to understanding his oeuvre, serving as living extensions of the themes explored in his static works while emphasizing the importance of direct action in effecting change.</p><p style="text-align:center;white-space:pre-wrap;" class=""><strong>Recording Art</strong></p><p style="text-align:center;white-space:pre-wrap;" class="">Beyond visual arts and performance art, EBC Studio opens up another dimension of soundscapes that complement visual narratives, providing a platform for other artists who share similar visions for social change through creative expression.</p><p style="text-align:center;white-space:pre-wrap;" class="">EBC serves as a collaborative space for musicians seeking innovative sounds rooted in profound messages about society—and another medium through which boundaries are pushed, nay destroyed entirely, conceptually (and technically).</p><p class="" data-rte-preserve-empty="true" style="white-space:pre-wrap;"></p><blockquote><p style="text-align:center;white-space:pre-wrap;" class=""><strong>“This studio is a space to inspire others within the artistic community and beyond towards greater introspection about our ever-evolving society!” </strong><em>Marlon Alexander Brown</em></p></blockquote></div>


  
